{{short description|American linguist}} {{Infobox academic|birth_name=Robert Thomas Harms|birth_date={{Birth year|1932}}|death_date={{Death date and age|2016|10|5|1932}}|alma_mater=[[University of Chicago]]|discipline=Linguist|sub_discipline=[[Phonology]]|workplaces=[[University of Texas at Austin]]}}
'''Robert Thomas Harms''' (1932 – October 5, 2016) was an American linguist and emeritus professor of [[linguistics]] at [[University of Texas at Austin]].<ref>{{cite web |title=In Memoriam: Robert T. Harms, 1932-2016 |url=https://www.linguisticsociety.org/news/2016/12/14/memoriam-robert-t-harms-1932-2016 |website=[[Linguistic Society of America]] |accessdate=2 November 2018}}</ref> He is known for his research on [[grammar of Estonian]] and [[phonological theory]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://liberalarts.utexas.edu/linguistics/faculty/in-memoriam/RobertTHarms.php|title=In Memoriam Robert T. Harms|last=|first=|date=|website=UT Austin Department of Linguistics|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|accessdate=2 November 2018}}</ref>
==Books== * ''Introduction to Phonological Theory'', 1968 * ''Estonian Grammar'', 1962 * ''Finnish Structural Sketch'', 1964
